article.headline: Boise St. 72, UC Santa Barbara 56
article.story: BOISE, Idaho -- Anthony Drmic led four Boise State players in double figures with 16 points, and the Broncos used a huge run at the end of the first half Saturday to roll to a 72-56 win over UC Santa Barbara. Jeff Elorriaga scored 15 points -- all coming on 3-point shots -- as Boise State (4-1) bounced back from a Tuesday loss at Michigan State. The Broncos went 9-of-18 from 3-point range. Igor Hadziomerovic scored 14 points and Derrick Marks had 10 for Boise State, which used an 18-0 run to turn a tenuous 19-18 lead into a 37-18 advantage. Alan Williams led UCSB with 15 points, and Taran Brown added 13 for the Gauchos (2-3), who turned the ball over 16 times and trailed for the final 36 minutes.
